methods.accept:
Provides a range to this consumer.  A false return value indicates that the application
 providing ranges to this consumer should not invoke it again.
 As consecutive calls to accept are made, delivered ranges are assumed to be non overlapping
 and increasing in their first value; in particular, the first of a range has to be strictly
 greater than the last of the previous range.

:param first: (long) - the range first value.
:param last: (long) - the range last value, inclusive.
:return: (boolean) false if don't want any more values after this one, true otherwise.
